late announcement? they've been censoring content for years, to the point of hiding them from search or failing to notify you. expecting anything different is folly. 
&nbsp;
only a f moron would agree with things such as "we will get rid of climate change deniers and anti-vaxxers", the thing is that these damaging conspiracy theories are debunked constantly from multiple sources with scientific data to back it up.

@Krixano: i only used that dichotomy as allegory to my argument that people don't simply abstracts open vs closed without a thought to an issue of good vs evil. that whole paragraph was about that.
now, credit is a legal issue as i mentioned previously, closed-source can help remedy it but its not the cure.

sure, some people ignore the benefits of closed-source because open-source is usually the goal, if there is profit to be made it should be within an open-source software, otherwise profit has a higher priority and closed-source may help with that. open-source software can also adhere to good-quality code in a timely fashion, and profit  making may be used as incentive for either open or closed.

@Rva: bluehub, kaffiehub, etc are only hubs but also a zite nonetheless, which may be confusing, but they aren't useful as a zite.

>Not sure if that's all I needed to do.


that's all you need to do, add other hubs.

i don't really know about spiritual ontology but many philosophical inquiries, fields, etc just fell out of the mainstream because there exist now more dominant ones.
&nbsp;
for instance old philosophical logic models aren't as useful as modern ones. Immanuel Kant demonstrated that inquires using old metaphysics are simply "unworldly", "mystical".
&nbsp;
qualia is one such concept, its mystical and can't reveal truths about the real world, only abstractions, so it fell out of fashion.
&nbsp;
although i don't know much about i love reading about philosophy of the mind. concepts such as p-zombies is just stupid (much like the Searle's chinese room) in modern times. we can more now than ever measure things precisely and accurately, it may be difficult but its just a matter of technology.

@draugrdeathlord@zeroid.bit:
>who know how to turn off and keep off the windows telemetry services

do you really trust that? i also turn it off and uninstall specific updates that contains telemetry, but still i wouldn't input any sort of financial information on a machine running windows. 
&nbsp;
its just easier to use linux or something like it. definitely not elementary os as the articles recommends though.

@draugrdeathlord@zeroid.bit: i understand that but i wouldn't be surprised if another "unexpected" windows rootkit came about, simply because its closed source, unfortunately many of these issues are also present on linux.


@ulrichard:  
>that it is hard to justify running Windows at all. 

driver stability, depending on your hardware and what you do linux drivers can be very unstable and lacking features. also gaming, very few games are cross platform and even less performs as well its windows counterpart. wine is great, not excellent nor perfect.

@Kaffie: take the classic RE games, many girls do stream it on twitch, i know you were talking about games made specifically for girls but the 21st century or so definition (connotation actually) of a girl. but more broadly speaking you will find more girls playing horror games then actions games, more animal crossing than minecraft, more survival horror than actual horror.
i would argue that its because that these games genres are at least more feminine than masculine.
plus, having females characters is a bonus because girls *tend* to prefer using female avatars, and boys males avatars.

@Kaffie: the games (and game genre) i mentioned do have feminine aspects rather than just female protagonists.
what you are looking for is really niche, but you mentioned games like animal crossing, you can always find similar games on the nds/3ds/switch like tomodachi like, story of seasons, rune factory, harvest moon, etc.
some other interesting games: Portal, broken sword, doki doki literature club.

@draugrdeathlord@zeroid.bit: that is a difficult question, everything happens within a context. we know that homosexuality wasn't allowed for a very long time in what we call today "the west" (generally speaking).
homosexuality as a word, its etymology comes with the context of same sex relationship, as a platonic object, abstract. in reality, if we didn't reify these objects, sex would be just sex, gender being irrelevant. 
&nbsp;
(which is controversial because the very reification came full circle to render the definition meaningless, historically speaking)
&nbsp;
practically speaking, sure, since man has a natural advantage, especially in more primitive societies.

@ulrichard: slaves and communism? do you mean soviet gulags? if so there is free market solutions to prison population that pretty much fall into the same definition working right now.

>Capitalism has evolved naturally from barter trade. Along the way enough people survived.

the mechanics of it? perhaps one could say that, but the *integration* is very different from the origins of something. also just for the sake of "not real capitalism" just remember this, there's been lots of, usually short-lived  [anarchic-socialistic-communistic communities](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_anarchist_communities) without a central government, never once a capitalistic one, it always needs coercion, dispossession to create a labor force, usually by landlords and the state (which is usually controlled by the elites).
